10 "§972.2. Protected health information of individuals receiving services
11 "A. For the purposes of this Section, the following terms have the meanings
12 ascribed to them in this Subsection:
13 (1) "Department" means the Department of Children and Family Services.
14 (2) "General contractor" means an organization designated by statute or
15 contract to manage the provision of pregnancy center resources through subcontracts
16 with organizations that directly provide pregnancy center services. "General
17 contractor" includes any entity designated to serve a similar function regarding a
18 pregnancy center program or initiative, regardless of the formal label used.
19 (3) "Pregnancy center" or "center" means a facility that provides
20 pregnancy-related services including but not limited to ultrasounds, pregnancy
21 testing, or pregnancy counseling; or that otherwise collects health information from
22 individuals who are seeking or receiving services from the center.
23 (4) "Protected health information" means any information related to an
24 individual's past, present, or future physical or mental health or condition that
25 contains information that identifies the individual or includes identifiable
26 information that could provide a reasonable basis to identify the individual.
27 (5) "Subcontractor" means an organization that provides pregnancy center
28 services in one or more locations by contract with the department or by contract with
29 a general contractor coordinating pregnancy center services or referrals under a
30 contract with the department.
31 C.(1) A pregnancy center, including a subcontractor operating or affiliated
32 with a pregnancy center, shall not disclose a client's name or protected health
33 information to any entity or individual outside of its organization without the written
34 permission of the client for that specific disclosure of information, unless the
35 disclosure is required by law.
36 (2) A pregnancy center shall provide to a client a privacy notice prior to
37 obtaining written permission for any disclosure of protected health information. The
38 privacy notice shall include all of the following:
39 (a) The specific purpose for disclosing the protected health information to
40 a third party.
41 (b) The specific types of protected health information to be disclosed.
42 (c) The third parties who might or will receive protected health information.
43 (3) A pregnancy center shall further provide a simple mechanism for a client
44 to revoke any consent previously granted for the disclosure of information.
