5 of a client related to a contract with a subcontractor or pregnancy center, or by virtue
6 of the relationship with such entities, shall not disclose the client's name or any
7 protected health information to any entity outside of its organization.
8 D. Nothing provided herein shall be construed to prevent a general
9 contractor or subcontractor from disclosing information that maintains the
10 confidentiality of an individual client, such as the number of clients who have been
11 provided with particular goods or services, or prohibiting disclosures as otherwise
12 required by or reasonably necessary for the department to exercise its oversight
13 authority.
14 E.(1) Any person who believes there has been a violation of the privacy
15 requirements of this Section has the right to file a complaint with the department.
16 (2) If the department has cause to believe a violation of this Section may
17 have occurred, the department shall investigate the matter and determine whether a
18 violation has occurred.
19 (3) If the department determines that a violation of this Section has occurred,
20 it shall further determine the responsibility of a general contractor or subcontractor
21 and shall initiate an enforcement action. An enforcement action may include any of
22 the following:
23 (a) A warning.
24 (b) An imposition of monetary fines.
25 (4) Any penalty assessed against a general contractor or subcontractor shall
26 be commensurate with the degree of responsibility attributed to that entity by the
27 department.
28 (5) Any action taken pursuant to this Section shall be in accordance with
29 applicable state contracting laws, rules, and procedures, including notice and an
30 opportunity to respond.
31 F.(1) The requirements of this Section apply to any organization that
32 receives state or federal funding, whether directly or indirectly, by contract, grant,
33 or other cooperative endeavor arrangement through a program or initiative managed,
34 monitored, or administered by the Department of Children and Family Services,
35 which provides payment for pregnancy center services, pregnancy center referrals,
36 pregnancy center marketing, or administrative functions of the program or initiative,
37 including but not limited to the Louisiana Pregnancy and Baby Care Initiative and
38 Thrive: The Baby and Parent Network.
39 (2) The general contractor or a subcontractor has the responsibility, along
40 with a pregnancy center, for ensuring the requirements of this Section are met with
41 respect to that center."
